The global Diisopropyl Adipate (DIPA) market was valued at USD 574.66 million in 2022 and is anticipated to reach USD 898.51 million by 2029, witnessing a CAGR of 6.63%% during the forecast period 2023-2029. The influence of COVID-19 and the Russia-Ukraine War were considered while estimating market sizes.



Diisopropyl Adipate (DIPA) serves as a vital organic compound in various cosmetic and personal care products. This colorless liquid boasts a mild odor and is classified as an adipic acid diester, resulting from the reaction of adipic acid with isopropanol.

